“As Far As You Could” by my husband in recovery, @charleskelley, is now available on all streaming platforms. Really grateful for the timing of this song ❤️ living with anyone in addiction is so painful, and the holidays can bring out the hardest aspects of that journey. 

This time last year i was waiting up for my husband who was deep in the grips of alcoholism, to come home from a night out. As i watched the minutes tick away in the early morning hours i just prayed that he would get in before our son woke up. Now, a year later, he is clear-eyed as he tucks him in bed at night. 

This song is part of Charles’ testimony to his life in recovery from alcohol addiction. It’s part of our family’s story. It’s the recovery that we wake up and ask God to help us walk every day. So if you are reading this, and you are in a hard place, please know that there is another way. 🙏🏻 You CAN feel peace. As a recovering codependent wife of an alcoholic, i am living proof that one day at a time in recovery can change a life. Sometimes the hardest thing to do is reach out, but there is a whole community in recovery that is waiting with open arms, to help you and your family. You are worth it and i love you. 

And i love you too, Charles Kelley ❤️

#recoveryispossible #recoveringoutloud #alanon

Bucket list gorilla trek in Volcanoes National Park in Rwanda with my #TravelFam 🇷🇼 💕🦍💯 

we walked about 4 miles round trip to the @kwitonda_family (19 gorillas, including 2 silverbacks and the youngest is 2 mos old). We spent an hour with them and got to see them snooze, eat, play, irritate each other, cling to their mommas, and swing from branches. To be this close to them was just incredible. Still processing it actually. What made it even more special was experiencing it with our guide, Francois, who has been doing this since 1981 with Dian Fossey. Seeing and hearing him communicate with the Gorillas was a reminder of how each life on earth is connected. 

Rwanda is SUCH a special country. It’s majestic and bountiful with the most amazing culture and people. The money raised from the permits for this trek go to supporting the surrounding communities, building schools, roads, houses, and the tourism provides hundreds of jobs. 

I feel SO beyond grateful to have this opportunity. What a day ❤️ #rwanda #volcanoesnationalpark

Rwanda, you are magic ✨ my travel fam started planning this trip about a year ago, in anticipation of 5 of us turning 40 this year and wanting to celebrate with an adventure. This was bucket list and WOW, was it incredible. @singita_ kwitonda is truly one of THE most special places I’ve ever visited, and the staff at Kataza House cared for us beyond measure (thank you Aimee, Gabi, Eric, Patrick, + team!)

We planned it with our travel agent @momentstravel who thinks of every detail + absolutely helped make this a trip of a lifetime (thank you, Annette + Nicole!)

The experience of seeing the @kwitonda_family up close will forever be a highlight, and sharing it with these six other women was perfection - it was absolutely exhilarating. Still traveling after 25 hours with one more layover and flight left so next up for me is SLEEP and snuggling my little guy, but it was worth every precious second. Thank you, Rwanda, for the beautiful experience 💙🇷🇼 #visitrwanda #volcanoesnationalpark #kwitondafamily #singitakwitonda #singita

Grammy awards through the years ⭐️ in LA, New York, Nashville, and Alys Beach. We’ve run the gamut of looks, sizes, youth and wisdom here haha. 

My fave memories include ordering room service cheese burgers at 5am after a night of celebrating @ladya’s 5 wins in 2011, borrowing @hillaryscottla’s earrings to go with my gold @hautehippieofficial dress in 2010, looking out over LA from the top of the Capitol Records building at the afterparty in 2012, cheering on Charles and his solo record nomination in front of the tv holding a days old Ward Kelley, bringing cutout Hillary to New York in 2018 (and anxiously awaiting the arrival of Betsy & Emory!), and making our homemade step & repeat with Wardy and getting dressed up at home in 2021. 

But above all really thankful to be on this ride with you, @charleskelley. We’ve celebrated through wins, losses, babies, burgers, and lots of years ❤️ Look at those two little KIDS on the red carpet 13 years ago haha. Can’t wait to cheer on all the nominees & performers tonight! #grammyawards @recordingacademy

Backstory for y’all: this amazing woman, @addieprattmusic is such a talented vocalist and songwriter…and also a @stjude miracle cancer survivor 💙 we met earlier this fall when she came to perform at a fundraiser for St Jude that @charleskelley and i hosted at our house. We were WOWED at her talent, and after her performance, @nathanchapmanofficial came up to our table and said “hey, i have an idea! Let’s auction off the opportunity for charles, Dave, and I to take Addie into the studio to record!” And everyone at the party showed up SO generously for St Jude, and made it happen for her to record some music 🙏🏻 

cut to a few months later, Addie wrote this song with Nathan, Charles, and @davehaywoodla - they recorded it a few weeks after that and HERE WE ARE! Addie is launching her career with this amazing song, weaving her journey at St Jude into her musical story. A magical nashville night that bloomed into being here now. 

I am so excited for you, Addie. YOU are magic ⭐️ cheers to the woman that you are and the story of hope you are bringing to the world ❤️

*Gratitude post alert* today marks a new era for @ladya as they kick off the #requestlinetour at @theryman! This morning in my quiet time i couldn’t help but reflect back to where we were as a family when this tour was originally supposed to start, last August. The way we were taking the smallest of baby steps and slowly but surely rebuilding our entire lives on a foundation of sobriety & recovery - where my tiniest shift in thoughts from control to peace seemed like moving a mountain. Today, April 14, marks roughly 9 and a half months of sobriety for @charleskelley. God quietly reminded me this morning that nine and a half months is the amount of time it takes for a human being to bring new life into the world. 

Full blown gratitude to be here for new life in family, marriage, career, music, body, mind, hope, trust, spirit, and peace. I can echo what Charles said yesterday, that this show is undoubtedly better today than it could have been last august 🙏🏻❤️ 

Thank you to everyone who has sent us words or encouragement, both publically and privately, and told us we can do this one day at a time. For every fan who said “don’t worry, we’ll be here for when you are ready…” And mostly to @hillaryscottla and @davehaywoodla for so lovingly holding us together by giving us time. Here’s to you, Lady A, for the gift your music brings to the world and your perseverance to bring this show to your fans. Let’s go have some fun! 💖

A few weeks ago we got to sit down with @gayleking and the @cbsmornings team to talk about what family recovery looks like from the disease of alcoholism. 

I know for me, getting help from all of the tools and groups (some of which i didn’t know existed 11 months ago!) has been truly life changing and life GIVING. Addiction is not easy to navigate - in fact it is very difficult to recover alone. It takes a community and every member of the family system moving toward healing, one day at a time. 

If you are struggling through this journey, YOU are not alone, and there is hope. We are still so early in our recovery and beyond grateful for everyone who has walked along side us (and carried us in many instances) taking tiny steps in the right direction. 

Thank you so much, @gayleking + @cbsmornings for letting us share this meaningful work. I’ll put the link in stories if anyone wants to watch 🙏🏻 

And @charleskelley i love you. 

As a friend told me “Shame cannot survive being spoken” and the opposite of addiction isn’t sobriety, it’s connection. 🙏🏻💖

Driving past the building where i lived when i moved to New York after college. The 1-bedroom apartment that i shared with 3 other roommates. The walls that held so many dreams and love and friendships and late nights and bank accounts with $5 to get through to the end of the month and heartbreaks and good choices and bad decisions and late-night McDonalds fries and the beauty of having no idea where life would take me. I think back to that young woman and am so proud of her, and thankful for the lessons - good and hard - that i learned in that apartment. It’s good to be young and it’s good to grow up in the concrete jungle where dreams are made of 🩷🩷🩷 #111Worth @walk721 @abbymmanning

My why: Ian Miller from Franklin, TN. Anna Miller, his mom. Every single Ian & Anna Miller who have walked through the front doors of St. Jude Children’s Research Hospital. 
When i had the opportunity to visit @stjude campus for the first time, i was a new mom and had heard that this place was special, but was anxious about what it would be like walking through the building - how painful would it be to see these sick kids? How could i look these mothers in the eyes as they hold their babies in a hospital while i get to tuck my baby into bed at home? 
I think it’s every moms worst nightmare to imagine hearing the words “your child has cancer” just like Anna did, and then holding your baby while he receives treatment 😭 
…And then i walked through the front doors of St Jude myself, and every picture of what i imagined it would be like was completely turned on its head. Yes, this is every parents worst nightmare, and also yes there is SO MUCH HOPE beaming through that building. Every family and patient that i met on that visit told me a version of the same thing: “there’s no place like St. Jude.” 
No family ever gets a single bill. Ever! Not for medicine, travel, food, lodging, not a single bill. Y’all, this is a global-leading hospital that is finding cures and new treatments for cancer daily, sharing every piece of data and research freely with any medical facility that asks, and it’s FREE. 
After that first visit i just knew i needed to do anything i could to help a place like @stjude. A place that takes the hardest pain and turns it into hope - for the Ian’s and Anna’s and the you’s and me’s. 
So that’s my why. To get to see an incredible young man stand up on a stage in front of a hundred strangers and bravely share his story of resilience and hope, and to thank God that a place like St. Jude exists. So thank you, Ian, for sharing your story. And thank you, God, for a place like St Jude. And thank you to every single person who showed up last night with their own “why” and helped us raise 1.8 million dollars to fund lifesaving care for these kids and their families. A night of silver linings 💙. #StJudeCurated

Merry Christmas! What a beautiful holiday it has been for our family. We are so blessed 🩷 i had a chance this morning to really take in every moment of joy and soak up this sweet season, because i remember when it wasn’t always so sweet. I know many families woke up this morning praying for help, peace, and sobriety. The holiday season can be an especially tough time for everyone struggling with addiction, and that pain ripples through every family & relationship. My hope is that if you are reading this and you are saying “yes, that’s me”, i want you to know that there is life & recovery on the other side and there are so many people willing to help you, one day at a time, and often one minute at a time. 

There is hope and people do recover, our family is proof. I am still so new to this journey but i know enough to know that we aren’t promised anything but today - and today i am grateful. Thank you, God, for recovery, and thank you, God, for bringing us the light of the world today - proving that light overcomes dark, and there is always redemption and hope. 🙏🏻🎄❤️
